cbsVrrpMIB.name: cbsVrrpMIB

revisions.description: Added cbsVrrpFailGrTable, cbsVrrpFailGrCompTable, cbsVrrpRemoteBoxPathTable and some new traps.

cbsVrrpMIB.contactinfo: Email: mib-admin@crossbeamsys.com Postal: 80 Central Street Boxborough, MA 01719
cbsVrrpMIB.description: XOS, Release 9.5: This MIB module defines the objects related to Crossbeam VRRP Traps.

cbsVrrpTrapNewMasterReason.name: cbsVrrpTrapNewMasterReason
cbsVrrpTrapNewMasterReason.description: This indicates the reason for NewMaster trap. Used by cbsVrrpTrapNewMaster trap.

cbsVrrpTrapNewMasterFailGrName.name: cbsVrrpTrapNewMasterFailGrName
cbsVrrpTrapNewMasterFailGrName.description: This object contains the VRRP Failover Group name. Used by cbsVrrpTrapNewMaster trap.

cbsVrrpTrapNewMasterVrId.name: cbsVrrpTrapNewMasterVrId
cbsVrrpTrapNewMasterVrId.description: This object contains the Virtual Router Identifier (VRID). Used by cbsVrrpTrapNewMaster trap.

cbsVrrpTrapNewMasterCirId.name: cbsVrrpTrapNewMasterCirId
cbsVrrpTrapNewMasterCirId.description: This object contains the circuit ID. Used by cbsVrrpTrapNewMaster trap.

cbsVrrpTrapNewMasterCirName.name: cbsVrrpTrapNewMasterCirName
cbsVrrpTrapNewMasterCirName.description: This object contains the circuit name. Used by cbsVrrpTrapNewMaster trap.

cbsVrrpTrapProtoErrReason.name: cbsVrrpTrapProtoErrReason
cbsVrrpTrapProtoErrReason.description: This indicates the reason for protocol error trap. Used by cbsVrrpTrapProtoError trap.

cbsVrrpTrapFailGrOldStatus.name: cbsVrrpTrapFailGrOldStatus
cbsVrrpTrapFailGrOldStatus.description: The old status for the failover group.

cbsVrrpTrapFailGrNewStatus.name: cbsVrrpTrapFailGrNewStatus
cbsVrrpTrapFailGrNewStatus.description: The new status for the failover group.

cbsVrrpTrapFailGrStatusChgReason.name: cbsVrrpTrapFailGrStatusChgReason
cbsVrrpTrapFailGrStatusChgReason.description: Indicates the reason of the status changed, e.g. 1. Down --> Master: Priority is 255 2. Down --> Master: Priority higher than remote box <id> 3. Down --> Master: Timed out waiting for master 4. Down --> Backup: Remote box <id> has higher priority 5. Down --> Backup: Master <id> has lower priority, but preemption is disabled 6. Master --> Backup: Relinquished by user 7. Master --> Backup: Preempted by remote box <id> 8. Master --> Down: Priority is 0 9. Master --> Down: Vrrp failover group is disabled. 10. Master --> Down: No valid virtual routers configured 11. Backup --> Master: Priority higher than remote box <id> 12. Backup --> Master: Priority is 255 13. Backup --> Master: Timed out waiting for master 14. Backup --> Down: Priority is 0 15. Backup --> Down: Vrrp failover group is disabled 16. Backup --> Down: No valid virtual routers configured

cbsVrrpTrapFailGrOldPriority.name: cbsVrrpTrapFailGrOldPriority
cbsVrrpTrapFailGrOldPriority.description: The failover group's old actual priority.

cbsVrrpTrapFailGrNewPriority.name: cbsVrrpTrapFailGrNewPriority
cbsVrrpTrapFailGrNewPriority.description: The failover group's new actual priority.

cbsVrrpTrapFailGrPriorityChgReason.name: cbsVrrpTrapFailGrPriorityChgReason
cbsVrrpTrapFailGrPriorityChgReason.description: This indicates the reason for PriorityChanged trap. Used by cbsVrrpTrapFailGrPriorityChanged trap. configured - configured priority changed vrDown - failover group down due to deleted/disabled or invalid configuration vrUp - failover group up due to becoming enable or valid virtualRouter - priority delta of involved virtual router changed verifyNextHop - priority delta of involved nexthop changed monitorCircuit - priority delta of involved monitored circuit changed monitorInterface - priority delta of involved monitored interface changed monitorGroupInterface - priority delta of involved monitored group interface changed activeVapThreshold - priority delta of involved active vap changed

cbsVrrpTrapRemoteBoxPathOldStatus.name: cbsVrrpTrapRemoteBoxPathOldStatus
cbsVrrpTrapRemoteBoxPathOldStatus.description: Old status of the specified path of remote box.

cbsVrrpTrapRemoteBoxPathNewStatus.name: cbsVrrpTrapRemoteBoxPathNewStatus
cbsVrrpTrapRemoteBoxPathNewStatus.description: New status of the specified path of remote box.

cbsVrrpRemBoxPathAddrs.name: cbsVrrpRemBoxPathAddrs
cbsVrrpRemBoxPathAddrs.description: All paths' IP addresses of the remote box, they are separated by comma.

cbsVrrpFailGrTable.name: cbsVrrpFailGrTable
cbsVrrpFailGrTable.description: This table contains information about the VRRP failover groups.

cbsVrrpFailGrEntry.name: cbsVrrpFailGrEntry
cbsVrrpFailGrEntry.description: An entry in the failover group table.

cbsVrrpFailGrID.name: cbsVrrpFailGrID
cbsVrrpFailGrID.description: The unique Group ID for the failover group.

cbsVrrpFailGrName.name: cbsVrrpFailGrName
cbsVrrpFailGrName.description: The name for the failover group.

cbsVrrpFailGrStatus.name: cbsVrrpFailGrStatus
cbsVrrpFailGrStatus.description: The status for the failover group.

cbsVrrpFailGrConfigPriority.name: cbsVrrpFailGrConfigPriority
cbsVrrpFailGrConfigPriority.description: The configured priority for the failover group.

cbsVrrpFailGrActualPriority.name: cbsVrrpFailGrActualPriority
cbsVrrpFailGrActualPriority.description: The actual priority for the failover group.

cbsVrrpFailGrEnabled.name: cbsVrrpFailGrEnabled
cbsVrrpFailGrEnabled.description: Specifies if failover group is enabled or not.

cbsVrrpFailGrPreemption.name: cbsVrrpFailGrPreemption
cbsVrrpFailGrPreemption.description: Specifies preemption for the failover group is off or on.

cbsVrrpFailGrLastChangeTime.name: cbsVrrpFailGrLastChangeTime
cbsVrrpFailGrLastChangeTime.description: Indicates the elapsed time since the status last changed.

cbsVrrpFailGrLastChangeReason.name: cbsVrrpFailGrLastChangeReason
cbsVrrpFailGrLastChangeReason.description: Indicates the reason of the status last changed, e.g. 1. Down --> Master: Priority is 255 2. Down --> Master: Priority higher than remote box <id> 3. Down --> Master: Timed out waiting for master 4. Down --> Backup: Remote box <id> has higher priority 5. Down --> Backup: Master <id> has lower priority, but preemption is disabled 6. Master --> Backup: Relinquished by user 7. Master --> Backup: Preempted by remote box <id> 8. Master --> Down: Priority is 0 9. Master --> Down: Vrrp failover group is disabled. 10. Master --> Down: No valid virtual routers configured 11. Backup --> Master: Priority higher than remote box <id> 12. Backup --> Master: Priority is 255 13. Backup --> Master: Timed out waiting for master 14. Backup --> Down: Priority is 0 15. Backup --> Down: Vrrp failover group is disabled 16. Backup --> Down: No valid virtual routers configured

cbsVrrpFailGrMasterSysID.name: cbsVrrpFailGrMasterSysID
cbsVrrpFailGrMasterSysID.description: The system ID of the platform that is operating as the master of this failover group.

cbsVrrpFailGrMasterPriority.name: cbsVrrpFailGrMasterPriority
cbsVrrpFailGrMasterPriority.description: The master failover group's actual priority.

cbsVrrpFailGrCompTable.name: cbsVrrpFailGrCompTable
cbsVrrpFailGrCompTable.description: This table contains information about the components of VRRP failover groups

cbsVrrpFailGrCompEntry.name: cbsVrrpFailGrCompEntry
cbsVrrpFailGrCompEntry.description: An entry in the VRRP failover group component table.

cbsVrrpFailGroupID.name: cbsVrrpFailGroupID
cbsVrrpFailGroupID.description: The ID of the VRRP failover group.

cbsVrrpFailGroupName.name: cbsVrrpFailGroupName
cbsVrrpFailGroupName.description: The name of the VRRP failover group.

cbsVrrpFailGrCompDescr.name: cbsVrrpFailGrCompDescr
cbsVrrpFailGrCompDescr.description: The detailed description about the component, the format depend on the type of the component, e.g.: vr - virtual router circuit name/virtual router id/OSPF cost increment mc - monitored circuit name mi - monitored interface mg - monitored group interface vg - vap group (active-vap-threshold) nh - verify-next-hop IP/virtual router ID

cbsVrrpFailGrCompDelta.name: cbsVrrpFailGrCompDelta
cbsVrrpFailGrCompDelta.description: The vrrp component's configured priority delta as well as information about its usage: 10 : priority delta of a component configured as 10 failover group priority NOT decremented by this delta (no failure) -10: priority delta of a component configured as 10 failover group priority decremented by this delta (component failure) 10* or -10*: unknown next hop status

cbsVrrpRemoteBoxPathTable.name: cbsVrrpRemoteBoxPathTable
cbsVrrpRemoteBoxPathTable.description: This table contains information about the path of VRRP remote box

cbsVrrpRemoteBoxPathEntry.name: cbsVrrpRemoteBoxPathEntry
cbsVrrpRemoteBoxPathEntry.description: An entry in the VRRP remote box path table.

cbsVrrpRemoteBoxID.name: cbsVrrpRemoteBoxID
cbsVrrpRemoteBoxID.description: The system ID of the VRRP remote box.

cbsVrrpRemoteBoxPathIndex.name: cbsVrrpRemoteBoxPathIndex
cbsVrrpRemoteBoxPathIndex.description: The index for path of VRRP remote box.

cbsVrrpRemoteBoxPathAddr.name: cbsVrrpRemoteBoxPathAddr
cbsVrrpRemoteBoxPathAddr.description: The path's IP address of the VRRP remote box.

cbsVrrpRemoteBoxPathLocalIntf.name: cbsVrrpRemoteBoxPathLocalIntf
cbsVrrpRemoteBoxPathLocalIntf.description: The path's IP address can be reachable via this local interface.

cbsVrrpRemoteBoxPathLocalAddr.name: cbsVrrpRemoteBoxPathLocalAddr
cbsVrrpRemoteBoxPathLocalAddr.description: The IP address of the local interface.

cbsVrrpRemoteBoxPathStatus.name: cbsVrrpRemoteBoxPathStatus
cbsVrrpRemoteBoxPathStatus.description: The path's status of the VRRP remote box.

cbsVrrpRemoteBoxPathLastChangeTime.name: cbsVrrpRemoteBoxPathLastChangeTime
cbsVrrpRemoteBoxPathLastChangeTime.description: Indicates the elapsed time since the status last changed.

cbsVrrpRemoteBoxPathLinkQuality.name: cbsVrrpRemoteBoxPathLinkQuality
cbsVrrpRemoteBoxPathLinkQuality.description: The link quality of the remote box path.

cbsVrrpTrapNewMaster.name: cbsVrrpTrapNewMaster
cbsVrrpTrapNewMaster.description: The newMaster trap indicates that the sending agent transitioned to 'Master' state.

cbsVrrpTrapProtoError.name: cbsVrrpTrapProtoError
cbsVrrpTrapProtoError.description: The error trap indicates that the sending agent encountered the protocol error indicated by vrrpTrapProtoErrorReason.

cbsVrrpTrapFailGrStatusChanged.name: cbsVrrpTrapFailGrStatusChanged
cbsVrrpTrapFailGrStatusChanged.description: The StatusChanged trap indicates that failover group of the sending agent transitioned from old to new state.

cbsVrrpTrapFailGrPriorityChanged.name: cbsVrrpTrapFailGrPriorityChanged
cbsVrrpTrapFailGrPriorityChanged.description: The PriorityChanged trap indicates that priority of the sending agent's failover group changed.

cbsVrrpTrapRemoteBoxPathStatusChanged.name: cbsVrrpTrapRemoteBoxPathStatusChanged
cbsVrrpTrapRemoteBoxPathStatusChanged.description: The StatusChanged trap indicates that one path of remote box on the sending agent's transitioned from old to new state.

cbsVrrpTrapRemoteBoxNoActivePath.name: cbsVrrpTrapRemoteBoxNoActivePath
cbsVrrpTrapRemoteBoxNoActivePath.description: The trap indicates that there is no active path for the remote box.

cbsVrrpTrapRemoteBoxNoSecondaryPath.name: cbsVrrpTrapRemoteBoxNoSecondaryPath
cbsVrrpTrapRemoteBoxNoSecondaryPath.description: The trap indicates that there is no secondary path for the remote box that contains 2 CPMs.

cbsVrrpTrapRemoteBoxNoStandbyPath.name: cbsVrrpTrapRemoteBoxNoStandbyPath
cbsVrrpTrapRemoteBoxNoStandbyPath.description: The trap indicates that there is 1 active path but no standby path for the remote box.

cbsVrrpTrapRemoteBoxPathSharedIntf.name: cbsVrrpTrapRemoteBoxPathSharedIntf
cbsVrrpTrapRemoteBoxPathSharedIntf.description: The trap indicates that all paths of the remote box only are reachable via single local interface on the sending agent.

cbsVrrpTrapNoRemoteBoxConfigured.name: cbsVrrpTrapNoRemoteBoxConfigured
cbsVrrpTrapNoRemoteBoxConfigured.description: The trap indicates that VRRP configured but there is no remote box configured.

cbsVrrpTrapOnlyOnePathDefined.name: cbsVrrpTrapOnlyOnePathDefined
cbsVrrpTrapOnlyOnePathDefined.description: The trap indicates that the remote box configured with only one path.

cbsVrrpTrapRemoteBoxRunLegacyXOS.name: cbsVrrpTrapRemoteBoxRunLegacyXOS
cbsVrrpTrapRemoteBoxRunLegacyXOS.description: The trap indicates that the remote box is running legacy XOS.
